title: 'The Girl in the Spider's Web' by David Lagercrantz tops Maclean's fiction list
text:
The Canadian Press - ONLINE EDITION 'The Girl in the Spider's Web' by David Lagercrantz tops Maclean's fiction list By: The Canadian Press 
Here are the top 10 hardcover fiction and non-fiction books in Canada for the week ending Oct. 18 as compiled by Maclean's magazine. The previous week's position is in parentheses. 
FICTION 
1. (1) The Girl in the Spider's Web _ David Lagercrantz 
2. (-) A Knight of Seven Kingdoms _ George R.R. Martin 
3. (2) The Heart Goes Last _ Margaret Atwood 
4. (5) The Illegal _ Lawrence Hill 
5. (6) The Murder House _ James Patterson and David Ellis 
6. (8) Undermajordomo Minor _ Patrick deWitt 
7. (3) Go Set a Watchman _ Harper Lee 
8. (7) Fates and Furies _ Lauren Groff 
9. (10) The Nature of the Beast _ Louise Penny 
10. (4) Make Me (A Jack Reacher Novel) _ Lee Child 
NON-FICTION 
1. (2) Why Not Me? _ Mindy Kaling 
2. (-) M Train _ Patti Smith 
3. (-) The Road to Little Dribbling: Adventures of an American in Britain _ Bill Bryson 
4. (3) Furiously Happy: A Funny Book About Horrible Things _ Jenny Lawson 
5. (1) History's People: Personalities and the Past _ Margaret MacMillan 
6. (5) The Reason You Walk _ Wab Kinew 
7. (7) Between the World and Me _ Ta-Nehisi Coates 
8. (4) Sixty: The Beginning of the End, or the End of the Beginning? _ Ian Brown 
9. (6) The White Road: Journey into an Obsession _ Edmund de Waal 
10. (9) The Art of Memoir _ Mary Karr
